ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Office PowerPoint ExtTimeNodeContainer Record Memory Corruption

EngDesc.value: A code execution vulnerability exists in Microsoft Office PowerPoint. The vulnerability is due to memory corruption while processing specially crafted PowerPoint files that contain a ExtTimeNodeContainer record. An attacker can exploit this vulnerability by enticing a user to open a specially crafted PowerPoint file. This can result in injection and execution of arbitrary code in the security context of the currently logged on user.
